  "body": "I found that zkSync does not use chainId when signing transactions, so how does zkSync prevent replay attacks?\r\n\r\n\r\nBelow is the signature message:\r\n```ts\r\ngetTransferEthMessagePart(tx: {\r\n    stringAmount: string;\r\n    stringToken: string;\r\n    stringFee: string;\r\n    ethAddress?: string;\r\n    to?: string;\r\n}): string {\r\n    let txType: string, to: string;\r\n    if (tx.ethAddress != undefined) {\r\n        txType = 'Withdraw';\r\n        to = tx.ethAddress;\r\n    } else if (tx.to != undefined) {\r\n        txType = 'Transfer';\r\n        to = tx.to;\r\n    } else {\r\n        throw new Error('Either to or ethAddress field must be present');\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    let message = '';\r\n    if (tx.stringAmount != null) {\r\n        message += `${txType} ${tx.stringAmount} ${tx.stringToken} to: ${to.toLowerCase()}`;\r\n    }\r\n    if (tx.stringFee != null) {\r\n        if (message.length != 0) {\r\n            message += '\\n';\r\n        }\r\n        message += `Fee: ${tx.stringFee} ${tx.stringToken}`;\r\n    }\r\n    return message;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nref: https://github.com/matter-labs/zksync/blob/f59e154865374bdc0f5ded2e2604dac599cb75ee/sdk/zksync.js/src/eth-message-signer.ts#L210-L239\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\nAn attacker taking someone's testnet(zkSync-ropsten) transaction, and repeating it on the mainnet(zkSync-mainnet). How dose zkSync prevent it?",
